00:13:48.704 --> 00:13:51.707
I mean. I'm kidding. It's a shitshow.
Everything's sore.

239
00:13:51.790 --> 00:13:55.002
And last week she cried because
they changed the Newsnight theme tune.

240
00:13:55.794 --> 00:13:59.214
She wants to get the leather saddle
on the rocking horse redone.

241
00:13:59.298 --> 00:14:01.466
- Do you know any good tanners?
- Uh. do you know what?

242
00:14:01.550 --> 00:14:04.094
I think we're between tanners
at the minute. so...

243
00:14:04.178 --> 00:14:08.182
You know. this kid doesn't even exist yet.
I've dropped two grand on it.

244
00:14:08.265 --> 00:14:10.976
Why can't we just have a baby
without all the...

245
00:14:12.644 --> 00:14:14.730
In other countries. they just have babies.

246
00:14:14.813 --> 00:14:19.860
You know. you go there. and there are.
like. babies just on the floor.

247
00:14:20.235 --> 00:14:23.173
They strap them to the front of their
tuk-tuks. and they drive around with them.

248
00:14:23.197 --> 00:14:24.781
They just get on with their lives.

249
00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:28.660
I mean. it's happened seven billion times.
It's not exactly a miracle.

250
00:14:28.744 --> 00:14:30.913
Having one
without starting a blog about it.

251
00:14:30.996 --> 00:14:32.331
That would be a miracle.

252
00:14:32.414 --> 00:14:33.415
All right.

253
00:14:34.208 --> 00:14:35.584
She wants yogurt.

254
00:14:36.293 --> 00:14:39.087
Does she want plain or Greek or what?

255
00:14:39.171 --> 00:14:42.007
It's for my wife's vagina. mate.
I'm not really fussed.

256
00:14:45.636 --> 00:14:46.929
Probably Greek then.

257
00:14:55.521 --> 00:14:56.730
- I know it's stupid...
- Mm.

258
00:14:56.813 --> 00:14:59.083
But is it possible
that they'll just give us one today?

259
00:14:59.107 --> 00:15:00.752
- At our initial information meeting?
- Yeah.

260
00:15:00.776 --> 00:15:03.946
- Yeah. We are pretty great.
- I know. right?

261
00:15:12.329 --> 00:15:14.581
Why does everyone look so miserable?

262
00:15:14.665 --> 00:15:16.208
Because it's a community center.

263
00:15:17.543 --> 00:15:19.395
Here we go.
Here's another one for the collection.

264
00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:22.339
We could always just move to the country
and raise our leaflets.

265
00:15:25.175 --> 00:15:26.552
He looks scary.

266
00:15:26.969 --> 00:15:29.471
Imagine getting him as your new dad.

267
00:15:29.555 --> 00:15:32.474
This says I need a BMI of under 35.
Have I got that?

268
00:15:32.558 --> 00:15:34.478
- I don't know. Is that good?
- It must be. yeah.

269
00:15:34.560 --> 00:15:36.019
No. probably not.

270
00:15:36.103 --> 00:15:37.145
Hello.

271
00:15:37.980 --> 00:15:39.940
- Would you like one of our packs?
- Yeah.

272
00:15:40.023 --> 00:15:42.401
It explains the process in more detail.

273
00:15:42.484 --> 00:15:44.945
Okay. How long does the whole thing
tend to take generally?

274
00:15:45.028 --> 00:15:47.322
- On average. around a year.
- Yeah.

275
00:15:47.406 --> 00:15:48.490
- A year?
- Wow.

276
00:15:48.574 --> 00:15:50.742
And then at the end of that.
then we get a baby?

277
00:15:51.285 --> 00:15:53.203
And then we begin the search.

278
00:15:53.287 --> 00:15:57.082
I should say. we don't really have babies.

279
00:15:57.165 --> 00:15:58.250
Oh.

280
00:15:59.293 --> 00:16:01.253
Will you be getting more in or...

281
00:16:01.336 --> 00:16:03.046
There are so few in the system.

282
00:16:03.130 --> 00:16:05.674
we do encourage you
to consider older children.

283
00:16:07.384 --> 00:16:08.844
- Excuse me.
- All right.

284
00:16:09.428 --> 00:16:10.429
Hello.

285
00:16:10.512 --> 00:16:12.312
- Would you like one of our packs?
- Hi.

286
00:16:12.347 --> 00:16:13.557
Hmm.

287
00:16:14.850 --> 00:16:17.186
I suppose I just didn't think
it would be so hard.

288
00:16:18.187 --> 00:16:20.272
Well. they are giving us a human.
aren't they?

289
00:16:20.355 --> 00:16:23.775
But it's a year of being.
like. brutally assessed.

290
00:16:24.276 --> 00:16:26.028
And they talk to everyone in your life.

291
00:16:26.111 --> 00:16:29.865
And then you have to sit in
on this big adoption panel.

292
00:16:29.948 --> 00:16:31.867
"Adoption Horror Stories."

293
00:16:31.950 --> 00:16:33.702
That looks nice and balanced.

294
00:16:33.785 --> 00:16:36.347
Jase. they're gonna come into our lives.
and they're gonna judge us.

295
00:16:36.371 --> 00:16:37.289
Well. so what?

296
00:16:37.372 --> 00:16:39.267
We don't even have lampshades
in all the bedrooms.

297
00:16:39.291 --> 00:16:41.210
You can't get kids
before you get lampshades.

298
00:16:41.293 --> 00:16:44.796
I just don't know
if it's worth going through all this.

299
00:16:44.880 --> 00:16:47.400
Are you saying all this because
they said we might get an older kid?

300
00:16:47.424 --> 00:16:48.884
- No.
- Huh?

301
00:16:50.594 --> 00:16:54.973
No. No. I mean. Jase. I'm barely
more than an older kid myself. am I?

302
00:16:56.266 --> 00:16:58.352
All right. well...

303
00:16:59.561 --> 00:17:01.396
If we can't have one of our own...

304
00:17:02.606 --> 00:17:05.858
and we don't want to adopt. then what are
we gonna do with the rest of our lives?

305
00:17:05.943 --> 00:17:06.944
I don't know.

306
00:17:08.487 --> 00:17:10.155
Join a sodding book club.

307
00:17:22.209 --> 00:17:23.377
- Would you like this?
- Yeah.

308
00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:24.461
Yeah.

309
00:17:29.216 --> 00:17:30.592
Thank you.

310
00:17:35.097 --> 00:17:40.978
Past par-ti-ci-ple.

311
00:17:41.395 --> 00:17:42.563
Past participle.

312
00:17:43.355 --> 00:17:46.108
Hello. You are through
to Vista Car Rental. My name is Nikki.

313
00:17:46.191 --> 00:17:47.526
How can I help you today?

314
00:17:48.151 --> 00:17:51.238
For me. it seemed to be
more about character than story.

315
00:17:56.201 --> 00:17:57.661
Yeah. I think...

316
00:18:13.302 --> 00:18:14.428
You all right?

317
00:18:24.605 --> 00:18:26.023
- This is delicious. Nikki.
- Yeah.

318
00:18:26.106 --> 00:18:27.542
- Well. thanks.
- What have you put in it?

319
00:18:27.566 --> 00:18:32.279
I put in it some tomato. garlic.

320
00:18:32.362 --> 00:18:34.740
onion. some chili peppers.

321
00:18:34.823 --> 00:18:39.119
courgette. anchovies. salt. sugar

322
00:18:39.203 --> 00:18:42.289
and just a little bit of emulsifier.

323
00:18:44.166 --> 00:18:46.710
So. uh. what's the news. guys?
How's things with you?

324
00:18:46.793 --> 00:18:48.045
Yeah. Fine.

325
00:18:48.962 --> 00:18:51.507
Lauren's been struggling a little bit
with the pregnancy.

326
00:18:51.590 --> 00:18:55.010
Well. obviously. I mean. for us. it's a
baby. For her. it's the enemy. you know?

327
00:18:55.093 --> 00:18:56.345
Yes. I know that.

328
00:18:56.887 --> 00:18:57.888
Oh.

329
00:18:58.472 --> 00:19:00.390
- Why are you doing that?
- What?

330
00:19:00.474 --> 00:19:02.601
Kissing on my forehead
like I'm your niece.

331
00:19:02.684 --> 00:19:04.478
All right. I was being tender.

332
00:19:05.187 --> 00:19:07.856
- Jesus.
- You all right? Chill out. Ceausescu.

333
00:19:07.940 --> 00:19:09.399
No. I think my water has just broke.

334
00:19:11.693 --> 00:19:13.087
- Oh. my God.
- Is that a real thing?

335
00:19:13.111 --> 00:19:15.507
- I thought it only happened in films.
- No. that's how you have a baby.

336
00:19:15.531 --> 00:19:17.383
- There you go. Yeah.
- Oh. shit. I haven't got the bag.

337
00:19:17.407 --> 00:19:19.451
- What? Why?
- Because I left it at home.

338
00:19:19.535 --> 00:19:20.970
I've got plenty of bags. mate.

339
00:19:20.994 --> 00:19:22.722
- All right.
- No. Jason. A hospital bag.

340
00:19:22.746 --> 00:19:25.099
- Should I call an ambulance?
- No. no. no. It's quicker to drive.

341
00:19:25.123 --> 00:19:26.959
- Oh. shit.
- What?

342
00:19:27.042 --> 00:19:29.920
- I've had three glasses of wine.
- How? We've been here for 20 minutes.

343
00:19:30.003 --> 00:19:32.798
I'll drive. and then I will go
pick up some stuff from your house.

344
00:19:32.881 --> 00:19:33.715
- Yes.
- All right?

345
00:19:33.799 --> 00:19:35.401
All right. That's good.
Lauren. darling. Come on.

346
00:19:35.425 --> 00:19:36.426
Right.

347
00:19:37.427 --> 00:19:38.428
All right?

348
00:19:39.221 --> 00:19:41.056
- Let's go have another baby.
- Come on. then.

349
00:19:41.139 --> 00:19:42.182
Oh!

350
00:19:45.602 --> 00:19:47.162
Hello. mate. I'm just at the house now.

351
00:19:48.188 --> 00:19:51.483
- Right. I'm in. Where do I go?
- In our room.

352
00:19:51.567 --> 00:19:54.462
It's on the chaise longue. That's the sort
of long chair thing by the window.

353
00:19:54.486 --> 00:19:56.321
I know what a chaise longue is.

354
00:20:00.617 --> 00:20:02.619
- Got it.
- Can you get Erica some clean knickers?

355
00:20:02.703 --> 00:20:05.023
That's the chest of drawers on the left.
middle top drawer.

356
00:20:18.969 --> 00:20:20.095
Got her knickers.

357
00:20:20.179 --> 00:20:21.513
And could you bring me a T-shirt?

358
00:20:21.597 --> 00:20:24.117
That's the other chest of drawers
second drawer from the bottom.

359
00:20:24.600 --> 00:20:25.684
Not the bottom.

360
00:20:26.810 --> 00:20:29.170
Did you get that? Not the bottom drawer.

361
00:20:30.189 --> 00:20:31.190
Jason?

362
00:20:38.530 --> 00:20:39.781
Jason.

363
00:20:42.451 --> 00:20:43.493
Hiya!

364
00:20:49.124 --> 00:20:52.544
This is exciting. isn't it?

365
00:21:00.802 --> 00:21:04.723
How... How are things with you?
Just. like. generally.

366
00:21:09.269 --> 00:21:10.395
You well in yourself?

367
00:21:16.652 --> 00:21:18.320
I'm hungry.

368
00:21:18.403 --> 00:21:19.446
Yeah?

369
00:21:21.615 --> 00:21:22.866
Let's have a see.

370
00:21:24.409 --> 00:21:25.577
Do you like trail mix?

371
00:21:26.620 --> 00:21:28.247
Do you have any chocolate?

372
00:21:30.791 --> 00:21:32.501
Why do you have chocolate in the car?

373
00:21:32.584 --> 00:21:36.797
Because if I keep it in the house.
I eat it.

374
00:21:36.880 --> 00:21:39.716
- You're meant to eat it.
- Yeah. I know. Adults are weird.

375
00:21:52.688 --> 00:21:54.398
Look. I get it.

376
00:21:54.481 --> 00:21:57.192
A baby means change. and change is scary.

377
00:21:58.652 --> 00:22:02.531
You don't know what they're gonna be like.
or if they'll even like you.

378
00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:10.080
But you can't get too attached
to what you think your life's gonna be.

379
00:22:11.373 --> 00:22:12.958
That's where your problems start.

380
00:22:15.836 --> 00:22:18.046
I think a baby will eat my yogurts.

381
00:22:19.756 --> 00:22:21.091
Right. Yeah.

382
00:22:21.800 --> 00:22:23.969
I mean. the yogurt stuff is always hard.

383
00:22:33.061 --> 00:22:36.773
"An aneurysm occurs
when the artery walls weaken."

384
00:22:37.399 --> 00:22:42.070
The pressure of the blood
beats against the weakened walls

385
00:22:42.154 --> 00:22:45.657
and makes them bulge. like a balloon.

386
00:22:46.408 --> 00:22:50.579
"An abdominal aortic aneurysm
can be dangerous."

387
00:22:51.622 --> 00:22:53.832
Well. she's half asleep.
She's only hearing tone.

388
00:22:55.417 --> 00:22:56.418
So?

389
00:22:57.252 --> 00:22:58.253
It's a boy.

390
00:23:01.381 --> 00:23:02.382
Yay.

391
00:23:06.178 --> 00:23:08.013
They're so vulnerable.

392
00:23:08.472 --> 00:23:10.057
They sleep so deeply.

393
00:23:10.140 --> 00:23:11.683
Yeah. it's 'cause they trust us.

394
00:23:12.392 --> 00:23:14.019
Idiots.

395
00:24:06.196 --> 00:24:08.365
Whee!

396
00:24:10.158 --> 00:24:12.327
Do you know what? I do really wanna do it.

397
00:24:14.121 --> 00:24:15.122
Do what?

398
00:24:16.832 --> 00:24:18.625
- "It."
- Oh.

399
00:24:21.545 --> 00:24:22.921
Okay.

400
00:24:23.005 --> 00:24:26.967
I just don't know if I have it in me.
They'll see I'm not ready and...

401
00:24:27.926 --> 00:24:31.013
Listen. listen. we've only gotta be better
than the previous parents. right?

402
00:24:31.096 --> 00:24:33.015
So even if we're average...

403
00:24:34.183 --> 00:24:36.435
we'll still look better in comparison.
won't we? Right?

404
00:24:36.518 --> 00:24:38.187
I'm not even average.

405
00:24:38.270 --> 00:24:40.272
- I'm a bloody mess.
- We're all a bloody mess.

406
00:24:40.355 --> 00:24:43.543
That doesn't give you a sick note out of
every bit of responsibility in your life.

407
00:24:43.567 --> 00:24:45.360
All right.
when did you become so fearless?

408
00:24:45.444 --> 00:24:47.571
I don't know.
I think I'm shedding fear with age.

409
00:24:47.654 --> 00:24:49.865
It's like all of the brain cells
that I'm losing

410
00:24:49.948 --> 00:24:51.575
are the ones that were holding me back.

411
00:24:53.619 --> 00:24:55.996
You got it stuck in the weeds!

412
00:24:56.079 --> 00:24:58.540
- It's not my fault.
- Oh!

413
00:24:59.416 --> 00:25:00.417
Can I try?

414
00:25:01.001 --> 00:25:03.003
No. it's mine. My toy.

415
00:25:03.086 --> 00:25:04.880
How do you know if you're ready?

416
00:25:05.464 --> 00:25:08.008
We waited until we were ready
once before. didn't we?

417
00:25:08.800 --> 00:25:10.886
And that turned out to be much too late.

418
00:25:15.766 --> 00:25:17.392
Oh. for God's sake.

419
00:25:19.478 --> 00:25:21.563
Where are you going?

420
00:25:21.647 --> 00:25:23.315
What are you doing? Nikki.

421
00:25:23.398 --> 00:25:24.958
- Give that to me.
- What are you doing?

422
00:25:24.983 --> 00:25:26.818
- Do you know how lucky you are?
- Get off!

423
00:25:26.902 --> 00:25:30.322
They are tiny little miracles.
Your 17 Twitter followers can wait.

424
00:25:30.405 --> 00:25:31.698
- Give it back!
- I'm sorry.

425
00:25:31.782 --> 00:25:34.535
I'm doing this for you
and for your children.

426
00:25:34.952 --> 00:25:38.705
- No!
- Talk to your children!

427
00:25:39.122 --> 00:25:40.666
They're not my children!

428
00:25:41.917 --> 00:25:43.710
- Mom?
- I...

429
00:25:45.754 --> 00:25:47.756
Oh! Just don't believe it.

430
00:25:47.840 --> 00:25:49.720
Oh. my God. your phone.
I threw your phone away.

431
00:25:49.800 --> 00:25:52.261
Jason. I threw his phone away.
I am so. so sorry.

432
00:25:52.344 --> 00:25:54.221
Now. look. I'm calling the police.
All right.

433
00:25:54.304 --> 00:25:56.807
Excuse me. excuse me.
Can I borrow your phone. please?

434
00:25:56.890 --> 00:25:58.350
- What are you doing?
- I don't know.

435
00:25:58.433 --> 00:26:01.395
I just saw him and the kids.
I think I'm just emotional because of...

436
00:26:02.062 --> 00:26:05.274
Shit! Jason.
we can't get a criminal record.

437
00:26:05.357 --> 00:26:07.860
They won't give us a kid.
It was in the leaflets.

438
00:26:10.654 --> 00:26:12.048
No. no. it's fine.
Just take your time.

439
00:26:12.072 --> 00:26:14.783
Do you really wanna do this?
Do you want to adopt?

440
00:26:14.867 --> 00:26:19.288
Yeah. Yeah. I think I might.
But I can't if I get bloody arrested.

441
00:26:19.371 --> 00:26:20.372
Thank you.

442
00:26:22.583 --> 00:26:25.460
Yes? Yeah. Hello. yes. Police. thanks.

443
00:26:26.461 --> 00:26:28.380
Uh...

444
00:26:29.882 --> 00:26:31.717
Sorry. mate. We're not bad people.

445
00:26:31.800 --> 00:26:34.160
- It's just a very complicated situation!
- Jason. just run!
